  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So all she had on that is addressed in her own handwriting and signature in her own handwriting, but it was a pre-printed postcard.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And while I didn't believe it, I wanted to believe it, that they are together and they are alive.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew-- we knew, and we doubted it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, you know, it's amazing, it's amazing how the desire to believe the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] impossible, sometimes, because it's so terrible to believe the truth.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We sometimes tend to believe the lies.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we-- we heard it already, while I was in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We already heard it because a lot of Polish kids that escaped from Poland, many of them escaped from the Warsaw ghetto, too.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where could they have gone?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They couldn't get to Russia, because that was the war front.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we did-- by that time, I joined, already, an underground, and we didn't whatever we could to assist them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because I spoke the language, I was at home, they were not.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had-- we did everything we could to protect them and get them out of Budapest to Romania, and from Romania there was another organization that took over.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Jewish organizations, the Jewish movement, has leased boats and-- through the Black Sea, they try to get in through-- through-- Iran-- through not Iran, but where the Black Sea borders.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Bulgaria, but then it borders-- the--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Turkey, through Turkey and tried to get into Palestine that way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Unfortunately, out of seven ships that I was instrumental-- or not singlehandedly-- but with the group that we were instrumental, out of seven, only two of them made it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "From what we have heard, that three of them sank, two of them were torpedoed by the English, and two of them made it through.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
